  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You may wear a Hauberk armor, Hide armor, or Mail Shirt as Light armor for the sake of determining proficiency. When wearing a Hauberk armor, Hide armor, or Mail Shirt, you can add 3, rather than 2, to your AC if you have a Dexterity of 16 or higher.</p><section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-ac7CapLrjEvEnsNM\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>Upon selecting this feat, if you don hauberk armor, a chain shirt, or hide armor and have a high enough dexterity bonus to qualify for the extra AC bonus, you will have to manually enable the effect provided to get the additional AC bonus.</p></section>",
